# Maintainer: Blueberry Linux <blueberry@mmzsigmond.me>
# Meta-package: pulls the GNU toolchain for building software on Blueberry.
# `bpm install base-devel glibc` gives a complete C/C++ dev environment —
# glibc is listed explicitly because the base image already provides its
# runtime, so bpm only lays down its headers/crt when you ask for it by name.
pkgname=base-devel
pkgver=1.0
pkgrel=1
pkgdesc='GNU toolchain meta-package (gcc, binutils, make, kernel headers)'
arch=('x86_64')
url='https://blueberry.linux/'
license=('MIT')
depends=('gcc' 'binutils' 'make' 'linux-api-headers')
package() {
  install -d "$pkgdir/usr/share/doc/base-devel"
  cat > "$pkgdir/usr/share/doc/base-devel/README" <<'EOF'
base-devel pulls gcc, binutils, make and the Linux API headers.

For a complete C toolchain that can compile and link against libc, also
install glibc (its headers + startup objects):

    bpm install base-devel glibc

glibc is requested by name because the base image already ships the glibc
runtime, so bpm treats it as provided and only installs its development
files when you ask for it explicitly.
EOF
}
